## Target

The target is `phenotype-go-sdk/packages/devhex` — the canonical absorption surface for any `devhex`-pattern content carried by `go-nippon`. This follows ADR-011 (HexKit devhex pattern absorption): HexKit, devhex, and the devhex-flavored work belong under `phenotype-go-sdk/packages/devhex` and any prior stand-alone `go-nippon` work would be folded into that package. Because the source payload is zero and the repo is already archived, there is no code to merge; the target exists to receive the *pattern* — i.e. if a future engineer were to recreate `go-nippon` work, it would land in `phenotype-go-sdk/packages/devhex` per the existing charter. The secondary consolidation target is `phenotype-infra` for any infra-side overflow, but since `go-nippon` was pure userland content (not infra), `phenotype-infra` is not the absorption target here.

